  Let <fr:tex>( x_n )</fr:tex> be a sequence and let <fr:tex>x  \in   \mathbb {R}</fr:tex>.

  The sequence <fr:tex>( x_n )</fr:tex> is said to <fr:strong>converge to</fr:strong> <fr:tex>x</fr:tex> if
  <fr:tex
display="block">\forall   \epsilon  &gt; 0. \  \exists  m  \in   \mathbb {N} . \  \forall  n  \ge  m. \  \left |  x_n - x   \right |  &lt;  \epsilon .</fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p>
  This is denoted <fr:tex>\lim _{ n   \to   \infty }{ x_n } =  x</fr:tex>.
